{{Infobox sport governing body |name = Antigua and Barbuda Amateur Bodybuilding and Weightlifting Federation |abbrev = ABABWF |logo = Antigua and Barbuda Amateur Bodybuilding and Weightlifting Federation logo.jpg |logosize = 225px |sport = [[Olympic weightlifting|Weightlifting]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = [[Antigua and Barbuda]] |founded = {{Start date|1965}} |aff = [[International Weightlifting Federation|IWF]] |affdate = |region = [[Pan American Weightlifting Confederation|PAWC]] |regionyear = |headquarters = [[St. John's, Antigua and Barbuda|St. John's]] |location = |president = Clayton D. Isaac |chairman = |chairperson = |chair = |chiefexec = |vicepresident = |director = |secretary = |coach = |womenscoach = |key staff = |operating income = |sponsor = |year closed = |replaced = |prevfounded = |url = |countryflag = Antigua and Barbuda }}
The '''Antigua and Barbuda Amateur Bodybuilding and Weightlifting Federation (ABABWF)''' is the [[Sport governing body|governing body]] for the [[sport]] of [[Olympic weightlifting|weightlifting]] in [[Antigua and Barbuda]].
==History== The body<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.flexxlabs.com|title = Bodybuilding Sponsors of the AWPCA|date = |accessdate = |website = |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> was founded in 1965 as the '''Antigua Weightlifting and Physical Culture Association (AWPCA)''' by Wesley Barrow. In 1985, the AWPCA's name was changed to the '''Antigua and Barbuda Amateur Bodybuilding and Weightlifting Federation (ABABWF)'''. Since then, the name was changed with a directive from the [[International Federation of BodyBuilding & Fitness|IFBB]] to the current name of Antigua Barbuda Amateur Bodybuilding and Weightlifting Federation.<ref>{{cite web|title=Antigua and Barbuda Amateur Bodybuilding and Weightlifting Federation|url=http://www.facebook.com/pages/Antigua-Barbuda-Amateur-Bodybuilding-and-Weightlifting-Federation/241400862652905|publisher=Facebook|accessdate=1 March 2013}}</ref>
