'''Oumar Samba Sy''' (born 8 December 1959) is a [[Mauritania]]n [[freestyle wrestler|freestyle]] and [[Greco-Roman wrestler]]

Sy competed for [[Mauritania]] in two Olympics, first at the [[1984 Summer Olympics]] where he competed in the [[Wrestling at the 1984 Summer Olympics – Men's freestyle 100 kg|100 kg freestyle]], he lost his first group match then withdrew from the competition, four years later at the [[1988 Summer Olympics]] he entered the [[Wrestling at the 1988 Summer Olympics – Men's Greco-Roman 100 kg|100 kg Greco-Roman]], he won his first group match with a fall against Maisiba Obwoge from [[Kenya]] in under two minutes, he then lost his next match and again withdrew from the competition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/sy/oumar-samba-sy-1.html|title=Oumar Samba Sy Bio, Stats, and Results|website=Olympics at Sports-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=2018-05-14}}</ref>

