{{Infobox football club | clubname = Parkvilla | fullname= Parkvilla Football Club | founded= 1966 | ground= Claremont Stadium, [[Navan]] | p.r.o= Ultan Coogan | chairman= Gerry Kennedy | manager= |Kenny Ratty assistant manager= |Mark Brady, Murt Doyle, Paudge Conway league= [[Leinster Senior League (association football)|Leinster Senior League]] Senior Division 1A | }}
'''Parkvilla Football Club''' are a [[association football|football]] club based in [[Navan]], [[County Meath]], Ireland. The club was officially formed in 1966. Parkvilla play their home games at Claremont Stadium, Navan. The club currently competes in the Leinster Senior League Senior Division 1B. Their reserve team competes in the Meath And District League.
Their youth teams play at the 'Ditch Pitch', on the Commons Road. They are said to be the most successful football club within [[County Meath]], [[Ireland]].
The senior side is currently managed by former [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] and [[Bohemian F.C.]] star [[Paul Byrne (footballer, born 1972)|Paul Byrne]].
