{{Infobox football club | | clubname = Tuz FC | | fullname = Tuz FC Football Club| | image = | | founded = 1990| | ground = [[Tuz Khormato]], [[Saladin Province]] | capacity = | chrtitle = President | chairman = | manager = | | league = [[Iraq Division 1]] | season = [[2012–13 Iraq Division 1|2012–13]] | position = Final Stage (4th Place) | current = }}
'''Tuz FC''' ({{lang-ar|نادي طوز الرياضي}}) is an [[Iraq]]i football team based in [[Tuz Khormato]], [[Saladin Province]]. Tuz has the largest [[Turkmen people|Turkmen Community]] in Saladin Province. [[Tuz (disambiguation)|Tuz]] is a word of Turkish origin which means "salt".
==2012–13== Currently Tuz is runner-up in the [[2012–13 Iraq Division 1]] Group A and in their way to qualify to the [[Iraq Premier League]].
